{"text":"I've fixed the Radix UI accessibility and ref errors. 

The warnings were occurring because the Dialog sub-components (`DialogOverlay`, `DialogContent`, `DialogTitle`, etc.) were missing `React.forwardRef`. Radix UI primitives rely on refs to manage internal state, focus, and accessibility. I've updated `/src/app/components/ui/dialog.tsx` to properly wrap these components with `forwardRef` and pass the refs down to the underlying Radix primitives, resolving the `SlotClone` render method error. 

Your luxury fashion design gallery's quick views should now open seamlessly without throwing those console warnings!","textMode":"visible_message"}
